<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFF9FFC6FF71FA8DFB76FA6F" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF9FFC6FF71FA8DFDF1FAD7" blockId="17.[151,1436,1338,1473]" box="[151,524,1374,1401]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFF9FFC6FF79FA8DFF05FAD7" box="[159,248,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="63.[151,250,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[202,1388,194,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-19@63.[190,1397,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURE 10. Eudocima salaminia and Eudocima discrepans group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605520/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 10</figureCitation>
: J, 19: K, 31: I, 25: H–J)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF9FFC6FF71FA51FB76FA6F" blockId="17.[151,1436,1338,1473]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
The pattern and sexual dimorphism is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF9FFC6FD56FA51FCBAFA33" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[688,839,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discrepans">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF9FFC6FD56FA51FCBAFA33" box="[688,839,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">E. discrepans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it can be separated as described above. It is found only on the large island of New 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFF9FFC6FE19FA75FDADFA6F" box="[511,592,1447,1473]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and surrounding smaller islands (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFF9FFC6FC2CFA75FB82FA6F" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Brou, V. A. &amp; Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J." box="[970,1151,1447,1473]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="152 - 166" refId="ref41849" refString="Zilli, A., Brou, V. A., Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J. (2017) The Eudocima Billberg, 1820 of the Australian Region (Lepidoptera: Erebidae). In: Telnov, D. (Ed.), Biodiversity, Biogeography and Nature Conservation in Wallacea and New Guinea. Vol. 3. The Entomological Society of Latvia, Riga, pp. 631 - 655, pls. 152 - 166." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Zilli 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF9FFC6FBE5FA75FBC9FA6F" box="[1027,1076,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
